{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: servicerequest-eu-lab_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH ServiceRequest instance conforming to the ServiceRequestLabEu
    profile. This resource represents a laboratory test order, linking the
    requesting practitioner, the patient, one or more specimen references, and
    any currently active conditions that serve as clinical reasons for the order.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: ServiceRequestLabEu
    Canonical : (EU lab ServiceRequest profile, IHE/HL7 Europe)
    Must-support elements covered:
      identifier, status, intent, code (lab procedure), subject, requester,
      specimen (array), reasonCode (from active conditions)

  NO HTML OUTPUT
    This template produces no HTML table rows and no HEAD rows. Both %%HEAD%%
    and %%HTML%% sections are intentionally left empty. The FSH narrative is
    set to `text.status = #empty` with a placeholder `text.div`, because a
    ServiceRequest carries no clinically meaningful human-readable content
    that is not already present on the referenced resources.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌────────────────────────────┬────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                   │ Type       │ Description                      │
  ├────────────────────────────┼────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                 │ string     │ Unique resource id; appended to  │
  │                            │            │ "Instance-ServiceRequest-" to    │
  │                            │            │ form the FSH instance name.      │
  │ srvqidentifier             │ string     │ Business identifier value for    │
  │                            │            │ the order (system:               │
  │                            │            │ http://example.org).             │
  │ patient.instanceid         │ string     │ UUID of the Patient resource;    │
  │                            │            │ used in the subject Reference.   │
  │ patient.name               │ string     │ Full display name of the patient;│
  │                            │            │ used as the Reference display.   │
  │ requester.instancerole     │ string?    │ Optional UUID of the requesting  │
  │                            │            │ PractitionerRole resource. When  │
  │                            │            │ empty, the requester element is  │
  │                            │            │ omitted entirely.                │
  │ specimenids                │ string[]   │ Array of specimen resource UUIDs.│
  │                            │            │ One specimen[+] Reference is     │
  │                            │            │ emitted per entry. The caller    │
  │                            │            │ must ensure these are deduplicated│
  │                            │            │ (see note below).                │
  │ conditions                 │ object[]   │ Array of condition records. Each  │
  │                            │            │ entry may contribute a           │
  │                            │            │ reasonCode[+] rule — but only    │
  │                            │            │ when the condition is active      │
  │                            │            │ (see Active-condition filter).   │
  └────────────────────────────┴────────────┴──────────────────────────────────┘

  CONDITION OBJECT STRUCTURE (one element of `conditions` array)
  ┌────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Key                            │ Type     │ Description                    │
  ├────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────┤
  │ active                         │ string   │ Encoded activity string in the  │
  │                                │          │ format "SYYYY-MM-DD" where S is │
  │                                │          │ a single-character status flag:  │
  │                                │          │   "1" = active condition        │
  │                                │          │   "0" = inactive / resolved     │
  │                                │          │ Only the first character is read │
  │                                │          │ (via `slice(0, 1)`).            │
  │ code.system                    │ string   │ FHIR CodeSystem URI (e.g. SCT). │
  │ code.code                      │ string   │ Concept code.                   │
  │ code.display                   │ string   │ Default display term.           │
  │ code.preferredTerm             │ string?  │ Optional override for the       │
  │                                │          │ display term; used in the FSH   │
  │                                │          │ reasonCode display if it differs│
  │                                │          │ from code.display.              │
  └────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────┘

  ACTIVE-CONDITION FILTER PATTERN
    The `conditions` array may contain both active and inactive/historical
    conditions. Only active ones are relevant as order reasons. Activity is
    encoded in the first character of the `condition.active` string:

      {% set activeflag = condition.active | slice(0, 1) %}
      {% set active = activeflag == 1 %}

    This extracts the leading status character before the date portion, then
    tests for equality with the integer 1 (active). Inactive conditions are
    skipped silently.

  PREFERRED TERM LOGIC
    For each active condition a display label is selected for reasonCode:
      1. Default: `condition.code.display`
      2. Override: `condition.code.preferredTerm` — used instead if it is
         non-empty AND differs from `condition.code.display`.
    This allows terminology servers to supply a locale-preferred label that
    overrides the raw SNOMED/LOINC display string.

  SPECIMEN DEDUPLICATION NOTE
    Multiple LOINC panel codes in the same order can map to the same physical
    specimen type. The caller is responsible for passing only unique specimen
    UUIDs in `specimenids`. The template itself performs no deduplication.

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct — SNOMED CT; 108252007 "Laboratory procedure" (fixed category code)
    Condition codes: system URI and code are taken from `condition.code.*`

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-08
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-ServiceRequest-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ServiceRequestLabEu
Title: "ServiceRequest"
Description: "ServiceRequest"
Usage: #inline
* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{#
  ── Business identifier ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  An order-level identifier, distinct from the resource id. System is a
  placeholder (http://example.org); real deployments should use a local OID
  or namespace.
#}
* identifier.system = "http://example.org"
* identifier.value = "{{ srvqidentifier }}"

{#
  ── Fixed status and intent ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All generated lab orders are active (not yet fulfilled) and represent a
  formal order (not a proposal or plan).
#}
* status = #active
* intent = #order

{#
  ── Fixed category code ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All instances of this template represent a laboratory procedure order.
  SCT#108252007 is used as the category code per the EU lab profile.
#}
* code = $sct#108252007 "Laboratory procedure"

{#
  ── Patient reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Links the order to the patient being processed.
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Requester reference (conditional) ──────────────────────────────────────
  The requesting PractitionerRole is optional. When `requester.instancerole`
  is empty (no practitioner is associated with the order), the element is
  omitted, which is valid under the EU lab profile.
#}
{% if requester.instancerole is not empty %}
* requester = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ requester.instancerole }})
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Specimen references ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  One specimen[+] Reference is emitted per entry in `specimenids`. The caller
  guarantees uniqueness; see the "Specimen deduplication" note in the file
  header. Two different LOINC panels may share a specimen type and would
  therefore share the same specimen resource UUID.
#}
{% for specimenid in specimenids %}
* specimen[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ specimenid }})
{% endfor %}

{#
  ── ReasonCode from active conditions ───────────────────────────────────────
  Iterates over all conditions passed in. For each condition:
    1. Extract the activity status flag from character 0 of condition.active
       (format "SYYYY-MM-DD" where S is "1"=active, "0"=inactive).
    2. Skip inactive conditions.
    3. Determine the preferred display term (preferredTerm overrides display
       when it is non-empty and different).
    4. Emit one reasonCode[+] FSH rule per active condition.
#}
{% for condition in conditions %}
{% set activeflag = condition.active | slice(0, 1) %} {# extract status char: "1" = active, "0" = inactive #}
{% set active = activeflag == 1 %}
{% if active %}
{# Resolve preferred display term: use preferredTerm if present and distinct #}
{% set preferred = condition.code.display %}
{% if condition.code.preferredTerm is not empty %}
{% if condition.code.display != condition.preferredTerm %}
{% set preferred = condition.code.preferredTerm %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

* reasonCode[+] = {{ condition.code.system }}#{{ condition.code.code }} "{{ preferred }}"

{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{#
  ── Intentionally empty narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────
  ServiceRequest carries no standalone human-readable narrative in this
  pipeline; all relevant information is on the referenced Patient, Specimen,
  and Condition resources. text.status = #empty is the correct FHIR status
  for a resource that deliberately omits narrative content.
#}
* text.status = #empty
* text.div = "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">intentionally left empty / not meaningful</div>"

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HEAD output — this template produces no HTML table. #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{# No HTML output — this template produces no HTML table. #}
